  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Landscape Innovation- East Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">While production continue to stagnate or dwindle in many parts of Sub Saharan Africa, there is a greater opportunity to work towards reversing the trend. Our believe that we can actually optimize production with lesser natural resource exploitation is the reason we have the adopted Landscapes Approach. Land degradation, water scarcity and loss of biodiversity are three important aspects that support  supply chain production. We can only sustain production if we conserve and rehabilitate our landscapes.</narrative>
  </description>
